<BaseLayout title="About — AIBolt Labs" description="AIBolt Labs builds open-source systems and practical software experiments.">
  <section class="page-hero"><div class="shell"><div class="eyebrow">About AIBolt Labs</div><h1 class="page-title">A place for software ideas that need to be experienced, not merely described.</h1><p class="lead">We explore how interfaces can construct themselves, respond with physical clarity, and remain usable across frameworks, inputs, and accessibility modes.</p></div></section>
  <section class="section"><div class="shell grid-3"><article class="card"><span class="number">01</span><h2>Experiment</h2><p>Start with a focused interaction question and build enough real machinery to test it honestly.</p></article><article class="card"><span class="number">02</span><h2>Document</h2><p>Publish the contracts, limitations, decisions, and examples that make the work understandable.</p></article><article class="card"><span class="number">03</span><h2>Elevate</h2><p>Turn the strongest experiments into dependable tools other developers can adopt independently.</p></article></div></section>
  <section class="section-tight"><div class="shell panel media-banner"><div class="media-banner-content"><div class="eyebrow">Built in the open</div><h2 class="section-title">Source, evidence, and iteration.</h2><p class="section-copy">AIBolt Labs projects are presented through working demos, public packages, and source repositories—not only concept imagery.</p><a class="button button-outline" href="https://github.com/aibolt">Explore GitHub ↗</a></div></div></section>
